</i></p><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-14_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Education is the cornerstone of a progressive society, enabling individuals to achieve their potential and contribute positively to the community. The Department for Education (DfE) is the UK governmental body that is tasked with overseeing education and children's services. In this blog, Dr Richard Dune explores the DfE’s role, highlights key facts and statistics, defines essential terms, and provides best practice recommendations for implementing relevant legislation and regulations. </span>
</p></div></div></div></div></div><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Previous" class="pf-slider-prev none hide"></button><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Next" class="pf-slider-next none hide"></button></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-5b6a" data-category="Collection Suggestion" data-name="Tea" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-kYHfwS doYKjf pf-16_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-hAcGzb cVhebe"><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-17_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-18_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-19_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-21_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-22_ pf-text-1"><strong>Budget and funding</strong> - In 2021-22, the DfE was allocated £104 billion, highlighting the government's significant educational investment.



</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-24_ pf-text-1"><strong>School attendance</strong> - As of January 2023, there were 8.9 million pupils in 24,400 schools in England.

</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-26_ pf-text-1"><strong>Higher education</strong> - Over 2.5 million students were enrolled in higher education institutions in the 2022/23 academic year.




 














</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-28_ pf-text-1"><strong>Early years education</strong> - The government provides 30 hours of free childcare per week for working parents of 3 and 4-year-olds, benefiting over 600,000 children annually.





 














</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-30_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-31_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-32_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-34_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-35_ pf-text-1"><strong>Department for Education (DfE) </strong>- The government department responsible for education and children's services in England.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-37_ pf-text-1"><strong>Legislation</strong> - Laws enacted by the government to regulate education and children's services, such as the Education Act 2002.




</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-39_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regulations </strong>- Detailed directives developed by governmental bodies to implement and enforce legislation.





</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-41_ pf-text-1"><strong>Compliance</strong> - Adherence to laws, regulations, and standards set by regulatory bodies, such as Ofsted and the Care Quality Commission (CQC).






</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-43_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-44_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-45_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommended best practice for implementation of relevant legislation and regulations
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-47_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-48_ pf-text-1"><strong>Understanding the legislation</strong> - Education providers must be well-versed in key legislation affecting the sector. This includes the Education Act 2002, which provides the legal framework for the organisation of schools, and the Children and Families Act 2014, which covers provisions for children with special educational needs and disabilities (SEND).

</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-50_ pf-text-1"><strong>Implementing regulations</strong> - Regulations are designed to ensure educational standards are met. Vital regulatory bodies such as Ofsted, which inspects educational institutions, and the CQC, which oversees care services, provide guidelines and standards that must be adhered to. Compliance involves regular training, updating policies, and rigorous internal audits.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-52_ pf-text-1"><strong>Role of compliance software</strong> - Utilising compliance management software, such as ComplyPlus™, can streamline the process of adhering to regulations. This software helps manage documentation, track compliance status, and ensure timely updates and training, reducing the risk of non-compliance.






</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-54_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-55_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-56_ pf-heading-1-h3">The role of the DfE in policy formulation
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-58_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The DfE formulates educational policies aimed at improving the quality of education. Recent initiatives include the introduction of T-levels, a technical alternative to A-levels, designed to prepare students for skilled employment. The DfE also plays a critical role in teacher training and recruitment, ensuring that schools are staffed with qualified professionals.





















</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-60_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-61_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-62_ pf-heading-1-h3">Regulatory oversight and quality assurance
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-64_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Regulatory bodies like Ofsted and the CQC operate under the aegis of the DfE, ensuring educational and care standards are maintained. Ofsted’s inspections provide an independent assessment of school performance, influencing public perception and funding decisions. The CQC ensures that care services, including those within educational settings, meet high standards of safety and effectiveness.























</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-66_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-67_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-68_ pf-heading-1-h3">Supporting vulnerable children
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-70_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The DfE is also tasked with supporting vulnerable children, including those with SEND. The Children and Families Act 2014 mandates tailored support plans for SEND students, ensuring they receive appropriate education and care. Schools and institutions must develop Individual Education Plans (IEPs) and work closely with families and specialists to meet these students' needs.
























</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-72_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-73_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-74_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommendations
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-76_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-77_ pf-text-1"><strong>Stay informed</strong> - Regularly update knowledge of relevant legislation and regulations.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-79_ pf-text-1"><strong>Use compliance tools</strong> - Implement compliance management software like ComplyPlus™ to streamline adherence processes.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-81_ pf-text-1"><strong>Ongoing training</strong> - Provide continuous staff training to ensure they know the latest compliance requirements.&nbsp;</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-83_ pf-text-1"><strong>Internal audits</strong> - Conduct regular internal audits to identify and address compliance gaps.





</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-85_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-86_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-87_ pf-heading-1-h3">Conclusion
